---
import WikiLayout from '../../layouts/WikiLayout.astro';
import WikiCallout from '../../components/WikiCallout.astro';
---

<WikiLayout title="The Stranger Guide">
  <h1>The Stranger Guide</h1>
  <p>Welcome to CURATIONS.DEV. If you are here, you are likely looking for a way to get ruthless, high-signal feedback on your public software project. This is not a social network. This is not a generic software directory. This is an execution and verification engine.</p>
  
  <WikiCallout title="The Core Mechanic">
    Submit a Project. Get ruthless, high-signal feedback. Leave with a better plan.
  </WikiCallout>

  <h2>1. What We Do</h2>
  <p>We provide a conversation-first Vibe Coding community. You bring a public GitHub Project and your working plan. You ask a human question. You receive human and explicitly requested AI guidance. You choose what to use. You return with a stronger plan or a revised Project.</p>

  <h2>2. The Visual Oracle</h2>
  <p>Everything you see here is intentional. The <code>2px</code> borders, the hard shadows, the brutalist layout. It is designed to be an editorial magazine for execution.</p>

  <h2>3. How to Start</h2>
  <p>Ready to jump in?</p>
  
  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a href="/submit/project/" style="display: inline-block; background: var(--near-black); color: var(--seasalt-white); padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; border: 2px solid var(--near-black); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);">
      [ Submit your Project ]
    </a>
  </div>
</WikiLayout>
